Moderate-to-vigorous exercise slows down our brain aging clock [1] and solves any bug in your code that you've been staring on for far too long.
Dear iAIMS friends, join us on Thursday the 22nd in Toronto in the early morning for a refreshing run along the lake!

iAIMS member Prof. Niels Bergsland mounts the stage in the NAIMS educational session at 8:30, which is why we will run early.
We will meet at "Ivy. Coffee Shop", close to the convention centre, and run on the "Martin Goodman Trail", a long cycling path along the lake.
Depending on the pace differences, we might make different pace groups on the spot.
We will run in the direction of the blue arrow, run for 15 minutes and then run back, meeting at Ivy. Coffee Shop again after half an hour.

